description: Collecting issues #7 & #8 of the blockbuster series, in which master storyteller J. Michael Straczynski and painter extraordinaire Marko Djurdjevic join forces for an explosive two-issue arc! Thor's never been more intense as he rules a newly glorious Asgard and all its people! But what danger has risen on the horizon of its American heartland surroundings? And how will Thor equip himself to face it?

Secrets are revealed as Captain America and the team go after Agent Bravo and Hydra!

Also: The Mandarin’s plan to utterly destroy Iron Man continues as the Golden Avenger is attacked by the Living Laser!

Plus: Thor lives! But the question is for how long?! Meanwhile, Tanarus and the Avengers battle Terminus!

Story and art by Ed Brubaker, Steve McNiven, Matt Fraction, Salvador Larroca, Pasqual Ferry and Pepe Larraz!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Vol.6 #2, Invincible Iron Man #511 and Mighty Thor Vol.4 #9!

76 pages!

"The Beautiful Ugly" part 1 of 3! Gotham City is great for tourists, but the locals know that you have to rule it, or it will rule you. When members of the Kingz gang start causing trouble on the subways, Batman has to teach them their place.
name: The Beautiful Ugly, Part 1 of 3

description: The Touareg are the knights of the desert. They can be gentle and kind, but if provoked, also fierce and unpredictable. For thousands of years they survived in one of the harshest climate of the world. But a recent war over the exploits of uranium mines has brought new hardship to the desert people. Persecuted by the surrounding countries, threatened by the ever-growing desert and economically depressed by the exploitation of their natural resources, one question remains to be asked: How are they supposed to survive?
name: The Uprising

description: Europolis is described in tourist brochures as the city of the future, and it's kind of true. It was built on the ruins of what was Brussels up until the 1950s, and it's obviously a model of modernity and progress. It's also the pride of the European United Nations, and famous for the super-hero defenders of justice who live there. But Europolis is also a city of greed and has the unfortunate reputation of being the capital of the world's super-criminals... In the heart of this city lives a warrior who is more than four thousand years old. She's descended from two Gods of War, but in modern Europolis, she's a lovely young woman, Sophia, who has chosen to give up her immortality to live a life of love and happiness with her husband and her little girl. But the super criminals of Europolis and her distant past soon force her back into battle along with the Justice Force...
name: The Lioness of Sparta

volume.name: Les Années Tolkien des Frères Hildebrandt

description: CMX/FLEX COMIX. With his horned head and pointed ears, young Kiichi resembles a demon. When his mother dies, he is ostracized from his village. Alone and with no clue to his true origin, he meets Mototaro, a traveling "Library Man" who goes from town to town, lending out books. When Kiichi spies some magical creatures literally jumping out of the pages of one of these books, he thinks he may be on the way to finding out where he came from. Mototaro and Hana – his young assistant – agree to let Kiichi accompany them. Together, they will encounter strange creatures and adventures while Kiichi tries to find his place in the world.
name: Vol. 1

description: In nineteenth century America, a mysterious island unknown to the rest of the world has citizens composed of outrageous capitalists, inventors, hucksters, and freemen, who jealously guard the island's fantastic wealth from the prying fingers of the outside world, even as they attempt to conceal its captivating secrets from one another. Enter the world of the Lost Colony in The Snodgrass Conspiracy, and see how the inhabitants confront the Native American Wars in The Red Menace.
